Santaco says while it understands that only taxi owners are allowed to apply, it encourages the money to be shared if possible with drivers also. The deadline for the applications is February 28th. eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - It appears the taxi industry nationally is not taking advantage of the Covid-19 Taxi Relief Scheme. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says a mere 10,000 taxi owners have applied so far. WATCH: Mbalula speaks on Taxi Relief Fund awareness drive He is now travelling across the country to encourage applications from the embattled industry. But taxi operators say the once-off payment is a drop in the ocean considering their daily struggles. WATCH: Taxi industry agrees to relief measures The deadline for the applications is 28 February and Mbalula said this date won't be extended * eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports.